            "answer_text": "When you add two negative numbers together, you \u201cadd the number parts\u201d, then keep the sign. (-8) + (-4) = (keep the negative sign) (8 + 4) = -12Whenever you add two numbers with the same sign, whether plus or minus, you add the numbers and keep the sign: (+8) + (+4) = (keep the plus sign) (8 + 4) = +12Next, you will see problems where you add numbers with different signs: When you add two numbers that have two different signs, you:keep the sign of the larger numbersubtract the smaller number from the larger number(-8) + (+4) = (keep the minus sign) (8 - 4) = \u2013 4(+8) + (-4) = (keep the positive sign) (8 - 4) = +4Practice more problems like this and it will get easier. ",
